contentrichtext.text: Two ships of the [[Royal Navy]] have been named '''HMS ''Fleetwood'''''; the latter named after the town of [[Fleetwood]]. A third ship was planned as ''Fleetwood'', but was renamed before being launched: *{{HMS|Fleetwood|1655|6}} was a [[Cavalier|Royalist]] ship captured by the [[Roundhead|Parliamentarian]]s in 1655 and renamed ''Wexford''. *HMS ''Fleetwood'' was to have been a [[Hunt class minesweeper (1916)|Hunt class]] [[minesweeper (ship)|minesweeper]]. She was renamed [[HMS Ford|HMS ''Ford'']] in 1918 and was launched later that year. *{{HMS|Fleetwood|U73|6}} was a [[Grimsby class sloop|''Grimsby'' class]] [[sloop]] launched in 1936 and broken up after 1959. ==References== * {{colledge}} {{Shipindex}} {{Italic title prefixed|3}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Fleetwood}} [[Category:Royal Navy ship names]]
